	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=60753><span id= >Soop</span></a><br><span id=notbold>113 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.40]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Aye, this is how is done... is this farming?&nbsp;&nbsp;Not in my definition.  This is getting good loot for alt.... Close to 'farming' is a guild going in and getting all the lower members a no drop item in the same way... this was done completely on Brell when the skellys were in tims deep.   is a type of farming but not complete.<br><br>Farming, defined by me as looting every spawn of something to make pp off of only while keeping those who can get exp from it from being able to hunt, (the high lvl mage that sits his pet in throne room of crushbone to loot cb belts while he takes the ones in the yard  or the high lvl that kills orc camps in ec or wc while lvl 10-12s sit and wait on him to finish)  that disgusts me, this is a difficult call...   That may change when I become 55 and wish to have a chance to get the item and some guild is hogging all the spawns for weeks on end, though getting exp... they are not allowing any others to benefit... to me that says something about their guild.   <br><br>I am not a 'play fair' advocate, per sey, but I am an advocate that if you get no exp off something... and someone else comes for camp... they get it (within reason), or you are in a place where someone would get exp by joining a group and have a chance at an item... and you have controll of the situation, it is fair to give them that chance.  They help kill... they get reasonable concideration on loot.<br><br>Guilds interaction with others outside a guild are near equal importance to those outside the guild... or should be anyway...   I personally have a list of guilds that do not consider others on Brell... and I will treat them accordingly when the time arises...   granted that does them little damage.. it is something that needs not be the case.<br><br>They will get no heals or ports, buffs for low lvl twinks, or special treatment i would give someone not affiliated with their guild... and i tell them such.  Is not against them personally ... just practices of members of their guild they usually benefit from.<br><br>Is this good, no and I do not like it.  But is the way that I make up for actions that have effected me or those close to me.<br><br>Farming of a superhigh zone... heh let the lvl 55-60s complain about it... heh.<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Mar 14 15:02:26 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Soop 53ish War<br>Brell<br><br>Pugette Tripsalott<br>61 Monk&nbsp;&nbsp;- Brell<br><br>Raynn Fahling<br>55 Druid - Brell</td></tr>
